A member of the Kwara state House of Assembly representing Patigi constituency, Ahmed Saidu Rufai has died. He was said to have passed on in the early hours of Tuesday at the University of Ilorin Teaching Hospital (UITH) after a brief illness This was disclosed in a statement by the media aide to the Speaker to House Salihu Yakubu Danladi, Sheriff Ibrahim The statement read: “it is with a heavy heart and total submission to the will of Almighty Allah that we announce the death of our colleague, Hon. Ahmed Saidu Rufai representing Patigi constituency “This is an unexpected situation that caught us in a rude shock, but unfortunately, the Almighty deprived us of the power to reverse such sad occurrence “As we struggle to live with this tragic development and the vacuum that comes with it, we pray that Allah in His infinite mercy forgive his shortcomings and give his family, the 9th Assembly, Patigi Emirate, friends and associates and Kwara state at large, the fortitude to bear this great loss.” Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.